@startuml MeetingRoomBooking_Annotated

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam ranksep 30
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam enum {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam interface {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

title <size:18>Teams Meeting Room Booking - Class Diagram (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "User searches for a 10-person room with projector, books 2pm-3pm, invites team, everyone gets notified."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE — BookingService
' ====================================================================
class BookingService <<Facade>> {
    - rooms : Map<String, Room>
    - bookings : Map<String, Booking>
    - roomSearchStrategy : RoomSearchStrategy
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    - calendarManager : CalendarManager
    --
    + searchAvailableRooms(criteria) : List<Room>
    + createBooking(request) : Booking
    + cancelBooking(bookingId) : void
    + modifyBooking(bookingId, newSlot) : Booking
    + getBookingsForUser(userId) : List<Booking>
    + getBookingsForRoom(roomId, date) : List<Booking>
    + setRoomSearchStrategy(strategy) : void
}

note top of BookingService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "User opens Teams and wants to book a room.
    Client calls BookingService — the **Facade**.
    It coordinates room search, calendar checks,
    booking creation, and notifications.
    One entry point for everything."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: USER + ROOM MODELS
' ====================================================================
class User {
    - userId : String
    - name : String
    - email : String
    - department : String
    --
    + getEmail() : String
    + getDepartment() : String
}

class Room {
    - roomId : String
    - name : String
    - floor : int
    - capacity : int
    - equipment : Set<Equipment>
    - location : String
    - isActive : boolean
    --
    + hasEquipment(equip) : boolean
    + getCapacity() : int
    + getFloor() : int
}

enum Equipment {
    PROJECTOR
    WHITEBOARD
    VIDEO_CONFERENCE
    PHONE
    LARGE_SCREEN
    SPEAKER
}

note top of Room #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - Core models.**
    "**User** = who books (name, email, dept).
    **Room** = what gets booked (capacity,
    floor, equipment like PROJECTOR,
    VIDEO_CONFERENCE, WHITEBOARD).
    **Equipment** enum lists room features."
end note

Room --> Equipment : has >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: TIME SLOT + CALENDAR (Conflict Detection)
' ====================================================================
class TimeSlot {
    - startTime : LocalDateTime
    - endTime : LocalDateTime
    --
    + getDurationMinutes() : int
    + overlapsWith(other) : boolean
    + contains(time) : boolean
}

class CalendarManager {
    - roomBookings : Map<String, List<Booking>>
    --
    + isRoomAvailable(roomId, slot) : boolean
    + getBookingsForRoom(roomId, date) : List<Booking>
    + addBooking(booking) : void
    + removeBooking(booking) : void
    + findConflicts(roomId, slot) : List<Booking>
}

note top of CalendarManager #C8E6C9
    **STEP 3 - Prevent double booking.**
    "**TimeSlot** has start/end and an
    overlapsWith() method for conflict checks.
    **CalendarManager** maintains all bookings
    per room. Before creating a booking,
    it checks isRoomAvailable(room, slot).
    If conflict found, booking is rejected."
end note

CalendarManager --> TimeSlot : checks >
BookingService --> CalendarManager : validates via >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: ROOM SEARCH — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
class SearchCriteria {
    - minCapacity : int
    - preferredFloor : int
    - requiredEquipment : Set<Equipment>
    - timeSlot : TimeSlot
    - preferredBuilding : String
    --
    + getMinCapacity() : int
    + getRequiredEquipment() : Set<Equipment>
}

interface RoomSearchStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + search(rooms, criteria, calendar) : List<Room>
}

class CapacityFirstStrategy {
    --
    + search(rooms, criteria, calendar) : List<Room>
}

class FloorPreferenceStrategy {
    --
    + search(rooms, criteria, calendar) : List<Room>
}

class BestFitStrategy {
    --
    + search(rooms, criteria, calendar) : List<Room>
}

note bottom of RoomSearchStrategy #FFE0B2
    **STEP 4 - How do we find the right room?**
    "User needs 10 seats + projector at 2pm.
    Multiple rooms might qualify. How to rank?"

    "**Strategy Pattern** — search logic is pluggable.
    **CapacityFirst**: smallest room that fits.
    **FloorPreference**: closest to user's floor.
    **BestFit**: scores by capacity+floor+equipment.
    Add CostBased strategy? One new class."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

RoomSearchStrategy <|.. CapacityFirstStrategy
RoomSearchStrategy <|.. FloorPreferenceStrategy
RoomSearchStrategy <|.. BestFitStrategy
BookingService --> RoomSearchStrategy : delegates search >
SearchCriteria --> Equipment : requires >
SearchCriteria --> TimeSlot : for slot >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: BOOKING + BUILDER
' ====================================================================
class Booking {
    - bookingId : String
    - room : Room
    - timeSlot : TimeSlot
    - organizer : User
    - participants : List<User>
    - currentState : BookingState
    - status : BookingStatus
    - subject : String
    - recurrence : RecurrencePattern
    - createdAt : LocalDateTime
    - observers : List<BookingObserver>
    --
    + confirm() : void
    + cancel(reason) : void
    + start() : void
    + complete() : void
    + addParticipant(user) : void
    + removeParticipant(user) : void
    + registerObserver(obs) : void
    + notifyObservers() : void
}

enum BookingStatus {
    CONFIRMED
    IN_PROGRESS
    COMPLETED
    CANCELLED
}

class RecurrencePattern {
    - type : RecurrenceType
    - interval : int
    - endDate : LocalDate
    - daysOfWeek : Set<DayOfWeek>
    --
    + getNextOccurrence(from) : LocalDate
    + isRecurring() : boolean
}

enum RecurrenceType {
    NONE
    DAILY
    WEEKLY
    BIWEEKLY
    MONTHLY
}

note top of Booking #FFCDD2
    **STEP 5 - Booking created.**
    "Booking is the **central domain object**.
    Has room, time slot, organizer, participants,
    and optional recurrence (daily/weekly/monthly).
    It participates in:
    - **State Pattern** (booking lifecycle)
    - **Observer Pattern** (notifications)"
end note

Booking --> Room : for room >
Booking --> TimeSlot : at time >
Booking --> User : organized by >
Booking --> BookingStatus : tracks >
Booking --> RecurrencePattern : repeats >
RecurrencePattern --> RecurrenceType


class BookingBuilder <<Builder>> {
    - room : Room
    - timeSlot : TimeSlot
    - organizer : User
    - participants : List<User>
    - subject : String
    - recurrence : RecurrencePattern
    --
    + room(room) : BookingBuilder
    + timeSlot(start, end) : BookingBuilder
    + organizer(user) : BookingBuilder
    + addParticipant(user) : BookingBuilder
    + subject(title) : BookingBuilder
    + recurring(type, interval) : BookingBuilder
    + build() : Booking
}

note bottom of BookingBuilder #D1C4E9
    **Builder for clean creation.**
    "Booking has 7+ fields. **Builder Pattern**
    gives a fluent API:
    new BookingBuilder()
      .room(room).timeSlot(2pm, 3pm)
      .organizer(alice).addParticipant(bob)
      .subject('Sprint Planning')
      .recurring(WEEKLY, 1)
      .build()"
    **Pattern: Builder | SRP**
end note

BookingBuilder --> Booking : builds >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: STATE PATTERN — Booking Lifecycle
' ====================================================================
interface BookingState <<State>> {
    + confirm(booking) : void
    + cancel(booking, reason) : void
    + start(booking) : void
    + complete(booking) : void
}

class ConfirmedState {
    + cancel(booking, reason) : void
    + start(booking) : void
    + confirm(booking) : void
    + complete(booking) : void
}

class InProgressState {
    + complete(booking) : void
    + cancel(booking, reason) : void
    + confirm(booking) : void
    + start(booking) : void
}

class CompletedState {
    + confirm(booking) : void
    + cancel(booking, reason) : void
    + start(booking) : void
    + complete(booking) : void
}

class CancelledState {
    + confirm(booking) : void
    + cancel(booking, reason) : void
    + start(booking) : void
    + complete(booking) : void
}

note bottom of BookingState #FFCDD2
    **STEP 6 - Booking lifecycle.**
    "**State Pattern** — each state is a class.
    **ConfirmedState**: can start or cancel.
    **InProgressState**: meeting ongoing, can complete.
    **CompletedState**: terminal, room freed.
    **CancelledState**: terminal, room freed."

    Confirmed -> InProgress (meeting starts)
    Confirmed -> Cancelled (user cancels)
    InProgress -> Completed (meeting ends)
    **Pattern: State | SRP, OCP**
end note

BookingState <|.. ConfirmedState
BookingState <|.. InProgressState
BookingState <|.. CompletedState
BookingState <|.. CancelledState
Booking --> BookingState : delegates lifecycle >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: OBSERVER + NOTIFICATION — Observer + Strategy
' ====================================================================
interface BookingObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onBookingUpdate(booking, eventType) : void
}

enum BookingEventType {
    CREATED
    CANCELLED
    MODIFIED
    STARTING_SOON
    COMPLETED
}

class ParticipantObserver {
    - user : User
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    --
    + onBookingUpdate(booking, eventType) : void
}

class RoomDisplayObserver {
    - displayId : String
    --
    + onBookingUpdate(booking, eventType) : void
}

class AuditLogObserver {
    --
    + onBookingUpdate(booking, eventType) : void
}

BookingObserver <|.. ParticipantObserver
BookingObserver <|.. RoomDisplayObserver
BookingObserver <|.. AuditLogObserver
Booking --> BookingObserver : notifies >

class NotificationService {
    - strategies : List<NotificationStrategy>
    --
    + notify(user, message) : void
    + notifyAll(users, message) : void
}

interface NotificationStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + send(user, message) : void
}

class EmailNotification {
    + send(user, message) : void
}

class TeamsNotification {
    + send(user, message) : void
}

class PushNotification {
    + send(user, message) : void
}

note bottom of BookingObserver #B2EBF2
    **STEP 7 - Everyone gets notified.**
    "On booking create/cancel/modify, Booking
    calls notifyObservers(). **Observer Pattern**:"

    "**ParticipantObserver**: notifies each user.
    **RoomDisplayObserver**: updates room screen.
    **AuditLogObserver**: logs for compliance."

    "ParticipantObserver uses NotificationService
    which has **Strategy Pattern** for channels:
    Email, Teams Chat, Push notification."
    **Patterns: Observer + Strategy | OCP, SRP**
end note

NotificationStrategy <|.. EmailNotification
NotificationStrategy <|.. TeamsNotification
NotificationStrategy <|.. PushNotification
NotificationService --> NotificationStrategy : delegates >
ParticipantObserver --> NotificationService : uses >
BookingService --> NotificationService : uses >


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "We traced: user searches rooms (**Search Strategy**
    ranks available rooms) -> builds booking via **Builder** -> calendar
    validates no conflict -> booking confirmed (**State Pattern**) ->
    participants notified (**Observer** + **Notification Strategy**) ->
    meeting starts/ends, state transitions automatically.
    5 patterns: **Facade**, **Strategy** (x2), **State**, **Observer**, **Builder**."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | User calls BookingService to search/book rooms | Facade | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | User, Room, Equipment models | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | CalendarManager checks TimeSlot conflicts, prevents double-booking | -- | SRP |
    | 4 | Find best room: smallest fit, preferred floor, best score | Strategy (search) | OCP, DIP |
    | 5 | Booking created with room, slot, participants, recurrence | Builder | SRP |
    | 6 | Confirmed -> InProgress -> Completed / Cancelled | State | SRP, OCP |
    | 7 | Participants, room display, audit log notified; via email/Teams/push | Observer + Strategy | OCP, SRP |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Search + Book** = Steps 1-5 | **Lifecycle** = Step 6 | **Notify** = Step 7 |  |
endlegend

@enduml
